node.text:
Tomorrow begins our first day of classes. In a year like no other, Columbia's campus is not just Manhattan-bound. It's located wherever our students are.

While we miss our Lions, we know they'll make the most of this moment. They are Columbia.

node.text:
Did you know the famous MGM logo is inspired by the Columbia Lions? ⬇️
•
In 1917, studio publicist Howard Dietz CC 1917 designed the “Leo The Lion” logo for Samuel Goldwyn’s Goldwyn Picture Corporation. He based it on the athletic team, the Lions, of his alma mater Columbia College.
•
When Goldwyn Pictures merged with Metro Pictures Corporation and Louis B. Mayer Pictures, the newly formed MGM retained the logo, perhaps the most famous studio logo in the world. 🦁💙
•
#ColumbiaUniversity #RoarLionRoar #ColumbiaAlumni #AlumniofColumbiaCollege #myccjourney #ccstateofmind

node.text:
New dual degree program announced! ⬇️
•
The College and @columbiapublichealth have launched an educational partnership that will enable qualified students to complete in five years both a Bachelor of Arts (BA) from Columbia College and a Master of Public Health (MPH) degree from Columbia Mailman. Find the full details via the link in our bio.
•
#columbiauniversity #myccjourney

node.accessibility_caption: Columbia College flags with Butler Library behind them.

node.text:
Did you know the College has 4️⃣ alumni who were Olympic flag bearers? ⬇️
•
African triple jump champion Nadia Eke CC'15 had the honor of hoisting Ghana's flag at this year's opening ceremony on July 23.
•
Sprinter Yasmeen Al Dabbagh CC’19 was a flag bearer for Saudi Arabia at the Tokyo games.
•
Sprinter Erison Hurtault CC'07 carried the Dominica flag at the London Olympics in 2012.
•
Fencer Norman Armitage CC 1927, SEAS 1929 was flag bearer for the U.S. in the opening ceremonies in 1948, 1952 and 1956!
•
#columbiauniversity #myccjourney #roarlionroar
